name: Dumbbell
details: Dumbbell exercises are more advanced as they require more stabilisation and activation muscles that might not get used in bilateral exercises,explains MH fitness editor Andrew Tracey.

name: Bench Press
details: An incline bench press allows you to move the back support upwards at an angle to target your chest, biceps, and shoulders.

name: Arm Curl Machine
details: This machine is best suited to commercial gyms unless you have a large space in your home to fit this machinery.

name: Cable Row Machine
details: This is a machine that allows you to do compound exercises. When working out, you sit on a padded seat and pull onto handles, which are attached to a cable, and the cable moves the weights.

name: Abdominal Bench
details: Abs, internal obliques, quadriceps, and transverse abdominal muscles.deltoids, triceps, hamstrings.

name: Ab Roller
details: Abdominals, deltoids, triceps, hamstrings, and lats.When moving the ab roller, make sure you keep your pelvis stable.
